<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910726-0055</DOCNO><DOCID>910726-0055.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Athlone Industries Inc.:   New Jersey Concern Posts   Quarterly Loss of $418,000</HL><DATE>07/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ATH</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Athlone Industries Inc., Parsippany, N.J., reported asecond-quarter loss of $418,000, or 12 cents a share, afternet income of $559,000, or six cents a share, a year earlier.Sales fell to $55.3 million from $57 million.   The company attributed the loss to a $3.7 million chargefrom discontinued operations. The company is trying toconcentrate on its core business, specialty steel, and hasshed its sporting goods and women's shoe businesses.</LP><TEXT>   For the six months, Athlone reported net of $2.1 million,or 27 cents a share, down 41% from $3.7 million, or 56 centsa share, in the 1990 period. Sales fell to $108.3 millionfrom $114.8 million. Athlone said the 1990 results includedearnings from discontinued operations of $1.7 million,largely a gain from the sale of its sporting goods business.</TEXT></DOC>